	<div itemprop="text"><p>Nice post Otto. It is a good example of just because you can do something, it doesn&#8217;t necessarily mean you should!</p>
<p>Plugin conflicts would be drastically reduced if all developers tried to keep up with best practices, and refactor their code when necessary. It makes sense as your support requests will be probably be reduced in the long term.</p>
<p>I try to do this with my own code if I find something that could be done better, or is just plain wrong. It&#8217;s a pride thing. And I take the view that I am continually learning rather than assuming I have nothing new to learn, just because my code &#8216;seems to&#8217; work OK. Or that a Plugin conflict must be someone else&#8217;s fault!</p>
</div>

