		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2012-05-16T00:12:59+00:00">May 16, 2012 at 12:12 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>[...] Although both will call your functions the same way, and you actually could — but never should! — apply add_action() to lists of filters and vice versa, or use apply_filters() instead of do_action() or even do_action() instead of apply_filters(), keeping them functionally and semantically separate is absolutely critical. As Samuel Wood says in “Actions and Filters Are Not the Same Thing”: [...]</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/actions-and-filters-are-not-the-same-thing/?replytocom=10839#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-10839", "10839", "respond", "646")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
